---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const configExample = `{
  "proxyPort": 8080,
  "uiPort": 8081,
  "dbPath": "~/.laurel-proxy/data.db",
  "maxAge": "7d",
  "maxDbSize": "500MB",
  "maxBodySize": "1MB",
  "certCacheSize": 500
}`;
---

<DocsLayout title="Configuration" description="Configure Laurel Proxy storage limits, auto-cleanup, proxy ports, and HTTPS certificate caching via config file or CLI flags." headings={[
  { id: "config-file", text: "Config File", depth: 2 },
  { id: "options", text: "Options", depth: 2 },
  { id: "size-and-duration-formats", text: "Size and Duration Formats", depth: 2 },
  { id: "auto-cleanup", text: "Auto-Cleanup", depth: 2 },
  { id: "related", text: "Related", depth: 2 },
]}>
  <div class="prose-custom">
    <p>
      Configuration is loaded from three sources, in order of priority (highest first):
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>CLI flags</strong> -- passed directly to the command</li>
      <li><strong>Config file</strong> -- <code>~/.laurel-proxy/config.json</code></li>
      <li><strong>Built-in defaults</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      CLI flags always win. Values not set on the command line fall back to the config file,
      and anything not in the config file uses the built-in default.
    </p>

    <h2 id="config-file">Config File</h2>
    <p>Create <code>~/.laurel-proxy/config.json</code>:</p>
    <pre><code>{configExample}</code></pre>

    <h2 id="options">Options</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Field</th>
          <th>Default</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>proxyPort</code></td>
          <td><code>8080</code></td>
          <td>Proxy listening port</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>uiPort</code></td>
          <td><code>8081</code></td>
          <td>Web UI and REST API port</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>dbPath</code></td>
          <td><code>~/.laurel-proxy/data.db</code></td>
          <td>SQLite database file path (supports <code>~</code>)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>maxAge</code></td>
          <td><code>7d</code></td>
          <td>Auto-delete requests older than this</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>maxDbSize</code></td>
          <td><code>500MB</code></td>
          <td>Auto-delete oldest requests when DB exceeds this size</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>maxBodySize</code></td>
          <td><code>1MB</code></td>
          <td>Truncate request/response bodies larger than this</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>certCacheSize</code></td>
          <td><code>500</code></td>
          <td>Max per-domain SSL certificates cached in memory</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="size-and-duration-formats">Size and Duration Formats</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Sizes</strong> accept raw bytes (<code>1048576</code>) or human-readable units
      (<code>1KB</code>, <code>10MB</code>, <code>1GB</code>).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Durations</strong> accept raw milliseconds (<code>86400000</code>) or human-readable units
      (<code>1s</code>, <code>5m</code>, <code>1h</code>, <code>7d</code>).
    </p>

    <h2 id="auto-cleanup">Auto-Cleanup</h2>
    <p>
      A background job runs every 5 minutes to enforce <code>maxAge</code> and <code>maxDbSize</code>:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Deletes requests older than <code>maxAge</code></li>
      <li>If the database still exceeds <code>maxDbSize</code>, deletes the oldest requests in batches</li>
      <li>Runs incremental vacuum to reclaim disk space</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This means you can leave Laurel Proxy running indefinitely without worrying about disk usage.
      The defaults (7 days, 500 MB) keep a useful history window while staying lightweight.
    </p>

    <h2 id="related">Related</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href={`${base}docs/getting-started`}>Getting Started</a> - Install and capture your first request</li>
      <li><a href={`${base}docs/cli`}>CLI Reference</a> - CLI flags that override config file values</li>
      <li><a href={`${base}docs/architecture`}>Architecture</a> - How configuration is loaded and applied</li>
      <li><a href={`${base}docs/https`}>HTTPS Interception</a> - CA certificate setup and certCacheSize tuning</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .prose-custom h2 {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-custom p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .prose-custom pre {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
  .prose-custom code:not(pre code) {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    padding: 0.125rem 0.375rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
  .prose-custom ul, .prose-custom ol {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-custom ul {
    list-style: disc;
  }
  .prose-custom ol {
    list-style: decimal;
  }
  .prose-custom li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .prose-custom em {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-style: normal;
  }
  .prose-custom strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }
  .prose-custom table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .prose-custom th {
    text-align: left;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  .prose-custom td {
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
